> The basic problem is that the data is in SPSS format. This is a proprietary binary (non-text) format of SPSS
> (https://www.ibm.com/uk-en/analytics/spss-statistics-software), which means it cannot be read using conventional
> tools (e.g. Excel, Matlab). 
>
> So, we need to convert it to a text format like CSV (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comma-separated_values). This
> format can be read in Excel, Matlab, etc. The R language is a bit like Matlab but don't worry about it for now - what
> is relevant is that it can convert the SPSS format to CSV. For now, I've converted the data pertaining to Part A,
> Section 7 which I mentioned earlier. Open this with Excel, and see if what I said previously makes a bit more
> sense. 
